Acatenango.label: Acatenango
Acatenango.description: Acatenango is a stratovolcano in Guatemala, close to the city of Antigua. The volcano has two peaks, Pico Mayor and Yepocapa which is also known as Tres Hermanas. Wikipedia

Acamarachi.label: Acamarachi
Acamarachi.description: Acamarachi, also known as Pili, is a stratovolcano located northeast of the volcanoes Aguas Calientes and Lascar, and southwest of the sector Salar de Pujsa of Los Flamencos National Reserve, in the Antofagasta Region of Chile. Wikipedia

Antuco (volcano).label: Antuco
Antuco (volcano).description: Antuco Volcano is a stratovolcano located in the Bío Bío Region of Chile, near Sierra Velluda and on the shore of Laguna del Laja. Wikipedia

Atna Peaks.label: Atna Peaks
Atna Peaks.description: Atna Peaks is an eroded stratovolcano or shield volcano in the Wrangell Mountains of eastern Alaska. Wikipedia

Bárðarbunga.label: Bárðarbunga
Bárðarbunga.description: Bárðarbunga is an Icelandic stratovolcano, or subglacial volcano located under the ice cap of Vatnajökull glacier, rising to 2,009 metres above sea level, making it the second highest mountain in Iceland, ... Wikipedia

Avachinsky.label: Avachinsky
Avachinsky.description: Avachinsky is an active stratovolcano on the Kamchatka Peninsula in the far east of Russia. It lies within sight of the capital of Kamchatka Krai, Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky. Wikipedia

Beerenberg.label: Beerenberg
Beerenberg.description: Beerenberg is a 2,277 m stratovolcano which forms the northeastern end of the Norwegian island of Jan Mayen. It is the world's northernmost subaerial active volcano. Wikipedia

Baekdu Mountain.label: Paektu Mountain
Baekdu Mountain.description: Baekdu, Paektu, or Changbai Mountain is an active volcano on the border between North Korea and China. At 2,744 m, it is the highest mountain of the Changbai and Baekdudaegan ranges. Wikipedia

Cerro Arenales.label: Cerro Arenales
Cerro Arenales.description: Cerro Arenales is a heavily ice-covered stratovolcano located in the Aysén del General Carlos Ibáñez del Campo Region of Chile, within Laguna San Rafael National Park. It towers over the southern part of the Northern Patagonian Ice Field. Wikipedia

Cerro Bravo.label: Cerro Bravo
Cerro Bravo.description: Cerro Bravo is a stratovolcano located in Tolima Department, Colombia, north of the Nevado del Ruiz volcano. Wikipedia

Corcovado Volcano.label: Corcovado Volcano
Corcovado Volcano.description: Corcovado Volcano is a stratovolcano located about 25 km south of the mouth of Yelcho River, in the Palena Province, Los Lagos Region, Chile. The glacially eroded volcano is flanked by Holocene cinder cones. Wikipedia

El Valle (volcano).label: El Valle
El Valle (volcano).description: El Valle is a dormant stratovolcano in central Panama and is the easternmost volcano along the Central American Volcanic Arc which has been formed by the subduction of the Nazca Plate below Central America. Wikipedia

Galunggung.label: Galunggung
Galunggung.description: Mount Galunggung is an active stratovolcano in West Java, Indonesia, around 80 km southeast of the West Java provincial capital, Bandung. Wikipedia

Kverkfjöll.label: Kverkfjöll
Kverkfjöll.description: The mountain range Kverkfjöll is situated on the north-eastern border of the glacier Vatnajökull in Iceland. With their glacier Kverkjökull, they are to be found between the Vatnajökull and the Dyngjufjöll. The mountains are still active volcanoes. Wikipedia

Koryaksky.label: Koryaksky
Koryaksky.description: Koryaksky or Koryakskaya Sopka is a volcano on the Kamchatka Peninsula in the Russian Far East. It lies within sight of Kamchatka Krai's administrative center, Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky. Wikipedia

La Grande Soufrière (volcano).label: La Grande Soufrière
La Grande Soufrière (volcano).description: La Grande Soufrière, is an active stratovolcano located on the French island of Basse-Terre, in Guadeloupe. It is the highest mountain peak in the Lesser Antilles, and rises 1,467 m high. Wikipedia

Momotombo.label: Momotombo
Momotombo.description: Momotombo is a stratovolcano in Nicaragua, not far from the city of León. It stands on the shores of Lago de Managua. An eruption of the volcano in 1610 forced inhabitants of the Spanish city of León to relocate about 30 miles west. Wikipedia

Mount Aragats.label: Mount Aragats
Mount Aragats.description: Mount Aragats is a large andesitic-to-dacitic stratovolcano in northwest Armenia about 40 km northwest of the capital city of Yerevan. It is the highest point in Armenia, located in the province of Aragatsotn, northwest from Yerevan. Wikipedia

Mount Adams (Washington).label: Mount Adams
Mount Adams (Washington).description: Mount Adams is a potentially active stratovolcano in the Cascade Range. It is the second-highest mountain in the U.S. state of Washington, trailing only Mount Rainier. Wikipedia

Mount Apo.label: Mount Apo
Mount Apo.description: Mount Apo is a large solfataric, potentially-active stratovolcano in the island of Mindanao, Philippines. Wikipedia

Mount Chōkai.label: Mount Chōkai
Mount Chōkai.description: Mount Chōkai is an active volcano located on the southern border of Akita and Yamagata in the Tohoku region of Japan, and is 2,236 m tall. Wikipedia

Mount Discovery.label: Mount Discovery
Mount Discovery.description: Mount Discovery is a conspicuous, isolated stratovolcano, lying at the head of McMurdo Sound and east of Koettlitz Glacier, overlooking the NW portion of the Ross Ice Shelf. Wikipedia

Mount Hood.label: Mount Hood
Mount Hood.description: Mount Hood, called Wy'east by the Multnomah tribe, is a stratovolcano in the Cascade Volcanic Arc of northern Oregon. It was formed by a subduction zone on the Pacific coast and rests in the Pacific Northwest region of the United States. Wikipedia

Mount Bona.label: Mount Bona
Mount Bona.description: Mount Bona is one of the major mountains of the Saint Elias Mountains in eastern Alaska, and is the fifth highest independent peak in the United States. Mount Bona and its adjacent neighbor Mount Churchill are both large ice-covered stratovolcanoes. Wikipedia

Mount Hagen (volcano).label: Mount Hagen
Mount Hagen (volcano).description: Mount Hagen, named after the German colonial officer Curt von Hagen, is the second highest volcano in Papua New Guinea and on the Australian continent, ranking behind only its neighbour Mount Giluwe which is roughly 35 kilometres to the southwest. Wikipedia

Mount Garibaldi.label: Mount Garibaldi
Mount Garibaldi.description: Mount Garibaldi is a potentially active stratovolcano in the Sea to Sky Country of British Columbia, 80 km north of Vancouver, Canada. Wikipedia

Mount Melbourne.label: Mount Melbourne
Mount Melbourne.description: Mount Melbourne is a massive stratovolcano that makes up the projection of the coast between Wood Bay and Terra Nova Bay, in Victoria Land of Antarctica. Wikipedia

Mount Karisimbi.label: Mount Karisimbi
Mount Karisimbi.description: Mount Karisimbi is an inactive volcano in the Virunga Mountains on the border between Rwanda and the Democratic Republic of Congo. Wikipedia

Mount Iliamna.label: Mount Iliamna
Mount Iliamna.description: NAME = Mount Iliamna | photo = MountIliamna.gif | photo_caption = View of the glaciated north flank of Iliamna Volcano. A typical plume of steam and gas rises several hundred meters above the fumarole field. Wikipedia

Mount Ngauruhoe.label: Mount Ngauruhoe
Mount Ngauruhoe.description: Mount Ngauruhoe is an active stratovolcano or composite cone in New Zealand, made from layers of lava and tephra. Wikipedia

Mount Pelée.label: Mount Pelée
Mount Pelée.description: Mount Pelée is an active volcano at the northern end of the island and French overseas department of Martinique in the Lesser Antilles island arc of the Caribbean. Its volcanic cone is composed of layers of volcanic ash and hardened lava. Wikipedia

Mount Nyiragongo.label: Mount Nyiragongo
Mount Nyiragongo.description: Mount Nyiragongo is an active stratovolcano with an elevation of 3470m in the Virunga Mountains associated with the Albertine Rift. Wikipedia
Mount Nyiragongo.type: Mountain in Democratic Republic of the Congo

Mount Pico.label: Mount Pico
Mount Pico.description: Mount Pico is a stratovolcano and the highest point on the Portuguese island of Pico in the Azores. Furthermore, reaching an altitude of 2,351 metres above sea level. Wikipedia

Mount Popa.label: Mount Popa
Mount Popa.description: Mount Popa is a volcano 1518 metres above sea level, and located in central Burma about 50 km southeast of Bagan in the Pegu Range. It can be seen from the Ayeyarwady River as far away as 60 km in clear weather. Wikipedia

Mount Rinjani.label: Mount Rinjani
Mount Rinjani.description: Mount Rinjani or Gunung Rinjani is an active volcano in Indonesia on the island of Lombok. Administratively the mountain is in the Regency of North Lombok, West Nusa Tenggara. Wikipedia

Mount Ruapehu.label: Mount Ruapehu
Mount Ruapehu.description: Mount Ruapehu, or just Ruapehu, is an active stratovolcano at the southern end of the Taupo Volcanic Zone in New Zealand. Wikipedia

Mount Scenery.label: Mount Scenery
Mount Scenery.description: Mount Scenery is a potentially active volcano in the Caribbean Netherlands. Its lava dome forms the summit of the Saba island stratovolcano. Wikipedia

Mount Süphan.label: Mount Süphan
Mount Süphan.description: Mount Süphan, is a stratovolcano located in eastern Turkey, immediately north of Lake Van. It is the second highest volcano in Turkey with an elevation of 4,058 m or 13,314 ft and has the second highest ... Wikipedia

Mount Merbabu.label: Mount Merbabu
Mount Merbabu.description: Mount Merbabu is a dormant stratovolcano in Central Java province on the Indonesian island of Java. The name Merbabu could be loosely translated as 'Mountain of Ash' from the Javanese combined words; Meru means "mountain" and awu or abu means "ash". Wikipedia

Mount Singgalang.label: Mount Singgalang
Mount Singgalang.description: Singgalang is a volcano in West Sumatra, Indonesia. Its elevation is 2,877 m. It is a twin volcano with Mount Tandikat, which is located to the south-south-west of Singgalang. However, only Tandikat has had historical volcanic activity. Wikipedia

Mount Tambora.label: Mount Tambora
Mount Tambora.description: Mount Tambora is an active stratovolcano on the island of Sumbawa, Indonesia. Sumbawa is flanked both to the north and south by oceanic crust, and Tambora was formed by the active subduction zone beneath it. Wikipedia

Mount Shishaldin.label: Mount Shishaldin
Mount Shishaldin.description: Mount Shishaldin is a moderately active volcano on Unimak Island in the Aleutian Islands chain of Alaska. It is the highest mountain peak of the Aleutian Islands. Wikipedia

Parinacota (volcano).label: Parinacota
Parinacota (volcano).description: Parinacota, Parina Quta or Parinaquta is a massive potentially active stratovolcano on the border of Chile and Bolivia. It is part of the Payachata volcanic group. The other major edifice in that group is the Pleistocene peak of Pomerape. Wikipedia

Savo Island.label: Battle of Savo Island
Savo Island.description: The Battle of Savo Island, also known as the First Battle of Savo Island and, in Japanese sources, as the First Battle of the Solomon Sea, and colloquially among Allied Guadalcanal veterans as The Battle ... Wikipedia

Ol Doinyo Lengai.label: Ol Doinyo Lengai
Ol Doinyo Lengai.description: Ol Doinyo Lengai, "Mountain of God" in the Maasai language, is an active volcano located in the Gregory Rift, south of Lake Natron within the Arusha Region of Tanzania. Wikipedia

Sakurajima.label: Sakura Island
Sakurajima.description: Sakurajima is an active composite volcano and a former island in Kagoshima Prefecture in Kyushu, Japan. The lava flows of the 1914 eruption caused the former island to be connected with the Osumi Peninsula. Wikipedia

Nevado Sajama.label: Nevado Sajama
Nevado Sajama.description: Nevado Sajama is an extinct stratovolcano and the highest peak in Bolivia. The mountain is located in the Oruro Department, Sajama Province, Curahuara de Carangas Municipality, Sajama Canton. Wikipedia

Shinmoedake.label: Shinmoedake
Shinmoedake.description: Shinmoe-dake is a volcano in Kagoshima Prefecture, Kyūshū, Japan, and a part of the Mount Kirishima cluster of volcanoes. It is believed to have formed between 7,300 and 25,000 years ago. Wikipedia

The Quill (volcano).label: The Quill
The Quill (volcano).description: The Quill is a dormant stratovolcano located on the island of Sint Eustatius in the Caribbean Netherlands. The summit elevation is 601 metres above sea-level.It is also the second highest mountain in the Netherlands. Wikipedia

Volcán de Fuego.label: Volcán de Fuego
Volcán de Fuego.description: Volcán de Fuego is an active stratovolcano in Guatemala. It sits about 20 miles from the colonial city of Antigua Guatemala, one of the Guatemala’s most famous tourist attractions. It has erupted frequently since the Spanish conquest. Wikipedia

Chimborazo (volcano).label: Chimborazo
Chimborazo (volcano).description: Chimborazo is a currently inactive stratovolcano located in the Cordillera Occidental range of the Andes. Its last known eruption is believed to have occurred around 550 AD. Wikipedia

Ulleungdo.label: Ulleungdo
Ulleungdo.description: Ulleung-do is a South Korean island far off the east coast of Korean Peninsula. Formerly known as Dagelet to the Europeans, Ulleungdo is about 120 km east of the Korean Peninsula. Wikipedia

Kronotsky.label: Kronotsky
Kronotsky.description: Kronotsky is a major stratovolcano of the Kamchatka Peninsula, Russia. It has a particularly symmetrical conical shape, comparable to Mount Fuji in Japan and to Mayon Volcano in the Philippines. Wikipedia

Lanín.label: Lanín
Lanín.description: Lanín is an ice-clad, cone-shaped stratovolcano on the border of Argentina and Chile. It forms part of two national parks Lanín in Argentina and Villarrica in Chile. Wikipedia

Brennisteinsalda.label: Brennisteinsalda
Brennisteinsalda.description:
The Brennisteinsalda is a volcano in the south of Iceland. Its height is about 855 m. It is situated near Landmannalaugar and not far from Hekla.
The name means in English sulphur wave. It comes from the sulphur spots which have coloured its sides. Wikipedia

Mount Erciyes.label: Mount Erciyes
Mount Erciyes.description:
Mount Erciyes is a massive stratovolcano located 25 km to the south of Kayseri in Turkey.
Erciyes is the highest mountain in central Anatolia, located within the ancient region of Cappadocia, with its summit reaching 3,916 metres. Wikipedia

Licancabur.label: Licancabur
Licancabur.description: Licancabur is a highly symmetrical stratovolcano on the southernmost part of the border between Chile and Bolivia. It is located just southwest of Laguna Verde in Bolivia. The volcano dominates the landscape of the Salar de Atacama area. Wikipedia

Mount Fuji.label: Mount Fuji
Mount Fuji.description: Mount Fuji, located on Honshu Island, is the highest mountain in Japan at 3,776.24 m. An active stratovolcano that last erupted in 1707–08, Mount Fuji lies about 100 kilometres south-west of Tokyo, and can be seen from there on a clear day. Wikipedia

Mount Etna.label: Mount Etna
Mount Etna.description: Mount Etna is an active stratovolcano on the east coast of Sicily, Italy, close to Messina and Catania. It lies above the convergent plate margin between the African Plate and the Eurasian Plate. Wikipedia

Mount Kilimanjaro.label: Mount Kilimanjaro
Mount Kilimanjaro.description: Mount Kilimanjaro, with its three volcanic cones, Kibo, Mawenzi, and Shira, is a dormant volcanic mountain in Tanzania. Wikipedia

Mount Kerinci.label: Mount Kerinci
Mount Kerinci.description: Mount Kerinci is the highest volcano in Indonesia, and the highest peak on the island of Sumatra. It is surrounded by the lush forest of Kerinci Seblat National Park, home to the endangered species of Sumatran Tiger and Sumatran Rhinoceros. Wikipedia

Adwa (volcano).label: Adwa
Adwa (volcano).description: Adwa is a stratovolcano in Ethiopia, located in the southern Afar region and has a 4 by 5 km caldera. Wikipedia

Reventador.label: Reventador
Reventador.description: Reventador is an active stratovolcano which lies in the eastern Andes of Ecuador. It lies in a remote area of the national park of the same name. Wikipedia

Bola (volcano).label: Bola
Bola (volcano).description: The Bola volcano, also known as Wangore, is an andesitic stratovolcano, located southwest of the Dakataua caldera. It is 1,115 metres tall and has a 400 metre wide summit crater. Wikipedia

Cosigüina.label: Cosigüina
Cosigüina.description: Cosigüina is a stratovolcano located in the western part of Nicaragua. It forms a large peninsula extending into the Gulf of Fonseca. Wikipedia

Cabeço Gordo.label: Cabeço Gordo
Cabeço Gordo.description: Cabeço Gordo is the highest mountain, massive stratovolcano and the largest geomorphological structure that forms the island of Faial. Wikipedia

Chinameca (volcano).label: Chinameca
Chinameca (volcano).description: Chinameca is a stratovolcano in central-eastern El Salvador. It lies north of San Miguel volcano and rises over the town of Chinameca. Wikipedia

Karkar Island.label: Karkar Island
Karkar Island.description: Karkar Island is an oval-shaped volcanic island located in the Bismarck Sea, about 30 kilometres off the north coast of mainland Papua New Guinea in Madang Province. The island is about 25 km in length and 19 km in width. Wikipedia

El Altar.label: El Altar
El Altar.description: El Altar or Kapak Urku is an extinct volcano on the western side of Sangay National Park in Ecuador, 170 km south of Quito. Spaniards named it so because it resembled two nuns and four friars listening to a bishop around a church altar. Wikipedia

Gunungapi Wetar.label: Gunungapi Wetar
Gunungapi Wetar.description: Gunungapi Wetar is an isolated volcanic island to the north of Wetar island in the Banda Sea, Indonesia. The island, a stratovolcano, only extends 282 m above sea level, but the total height of the summit from the sea bed is over 5000 m. Wikipedia

Mount Gharat.label: Mount Gharat
Mount Gharat.description: Mount Gharat or Mount Garet is the highest peak on the volcanic island of Gaua of the Banks Islands in northern Vanuatu. Wikipedia

Mount Manuk.label: Manuk
Mount Manuk.description:
Manuk is an uninhabited volcanic island located in the Banda Sea, Indonesia. Administratively it is part of the Maluku Tengah Regency, Maluku Province.
Manuk means bird in Javanese and Sundanese. Wikipedia

Mare Island (Indonesia).label: Mare Island
Mare Island (Indonesia).description: Mare is a small volcanic island at the west side of Halmahera island, Indonesia. The 2 × 3 km island is part of the volcanic arc chain of Halmahera volcanoes. Wikipedia

Mount Nila.label: Mount Nila
Mount Nila.description: Nila volcano forms completely an isolated 5 × 6 km wide of island with the same name in the Barat Daya Islands of the Banda Sea, Indonesia. The volcano comprises a low caldera with its rims breach into the sea surface on the south and the east side. Wikipedia

Moti Island.label: Moti Island
Moti Island.description: Moti or Motir is a volcanic island in the western side of Halmahera island, Indonesia. The 5 km wide island is surrounded by coral reefs. Its summit is truncated and the volcano contains a crater at the southwest side. Wikipedia

Nemrut (volcano).label: Nemrut
Nemrut (volcano).description:
Nemrut is a dormant volcano in Eastern Turkey, close to Lake Van. The volcano is named after King Nimrod who is said to have ruled this area in about 2100 BC.
The most powerful eruptions of Nemrut occurred in the Pleistocene. Wikipedia

Mount Teon.label: Mount Teon
Mount Teon.description: Mount Teon is an elongated island in the Banda Sea, Indonesia. Explosive eruptions have been recorded from the volcano since the seventeenth century. Wikipedia

Tanga Islands.label: Tanga Islands
Tanga Islands.description: The Tanga Islands are an island group in Papua New Guinea, located northeast of New Ireland and part of the Bismarck Archipelago. The islands are the remnants of a stratovolcano which collapsed to form a caldera. Wikipedia

Ulawun.label: Ulawun
Ulawun.description: Ulawun is a basaltic and andesitic stratovolcano situated on the island of New Britain, Papua New Guinea, about 130 km southwest of Rabaul. Wikipedia

Hualca Hualca.label: Wallqa Wallqa
Hualca Hualca.description: Wallqa Wallqa is a volcano in the Andes of Peru. It has a height of 6,025 metres. Wikipedia

Akademia Nauk (volcano).label: Akademia Nauk
Akademia Nauk (volcano).description: Akademia Nauk is a volcano located in the southern part of Kamchatka Peninsula, Russia. The volcano is filled with a few calderas, and the most notable one is known as Karymsky Lake. Wikipedia

Amak Volcano.label: Amak Volcano
Amak Volcano.description: Amak Volcano is a basaltic andesite stratovolcano in the Aleutian Islands of Alaska, USA, 618 miles from Anchorage. It is located on the eponymous island, 31 miles from Frosty Volcano and near the edge of the Alaskan Peninsula's western flank. Wikipedia

Almolonga.label: Almolonga, Quetzaltenango
Almolonga.description: Almolonga is a municipality in the Quetzaltenango Department of Guatemala, located on the road between Ciudad de Quetzaltenango and Zunil. Wikipedia

Aucanquilcha.label: Aucanquilcha
Aucanquilcha.description: Aucanquilcha is a massive stratovolcano located in Antofagasta Region of northern Chile, just west of the border with Bolivia. It comprises a number of overlapping cones along a 10 km long ridge that forms the summit. Wikipedia

Babase Island.label: Babase Island
Babase Island.description: Babase Island is an island of the Feni Islands in Papua New Guinea, located east of New Ireland. It consists of a stratovolcano and a lava dome, joined by an isthmus. Wikipedia

Atsonupuri.label: Atsonupuri
Atsonupuri.description: Atsonupuri is a stratovolcano located in the central part of Iturup Island, Kuril Islands, Russia. Wikipedia

Babuyan Claro.label: Babuyan Claro Volcano
Babuyan Claro.description: Babuyan Claro Volcano, also known as Mount Pangasun, is a volcano located on Babuyan Island, the northernmost of the Babuyan group of islands in Luzon Strait, north of the main island of Luzon in the Philippines. Wikipedia

Batu Tara.label: Batu Tara
Batu Tara.description: Batu Tara stratovolcano is a small isolated island in the Flores Sea in Indonesia. Vegetations covers the flanks of Batu Tara. The first historical eruption occurred in 1852 with explosions and lava flows. Wikipedia

Antofalla.label: Antofalla
Antofalla.description: Antofalla is a large and very remote stratovolcano in Catamarca Province in northwestern Argentina. It is located on the northeastern edge of the Puna de Atacama, a high desert plateau east of the Atacama Desert. Wikipedia

Balatukan.label: Mount Balatukan
Balatukan.description: Mount Balatukan is a massive compound stratovolcano in the southern island of Mindanao, Philippines. The volcano has no historical eruptions but displays fumarolic activity. Wikipedia

Belenkaya.label: Belenkaya
Belenkaya.description: Belenkaya is a stratovolcano located in the southern part of Kamchatka Peninsula, Russia. Wikipedia
